features: ♻ Safe Charging: Because most interface devices equipped with Micro USB have been released for a long time, for the safety and reliability of the battery, we will control the maximum output power and current of the wire for stable charging. This can extend the service life of the battery. If your charger and device support fast charging protocol, our data cable still supports QC 2.0 fast charging protocol: 5V-2A, 9V-2A, 12V-1.5A with a maximum output of 18w power.

🔄 High-speed transmission: Support USB 2.0 bus protocol specifications proposed by USB-IF organizations on April 27, 2000, with a high-speed transmission rate of 480 Mbit/s (60MB/s), down compatible with low-speed 1.5 Mbit/s and full-speed 12 Mbit/s. After laboratory testing, during continuous transmission, the average transmission speed of 6ft-length data cables can reach 38MB/s and the peak speed is 44MB/s. Efficiently transfer or synchronize documents, photos, songs, movies, and other files.

📱Compatibility List: Micro-USB Port Compatible with Smartphone, Tablets, Kindle, Game Consoles, MP4 players, Speakers, Cameras, Hard drives, E-readers, PowerBank and all Other Micro-USB connecting devices. Hope this helps you.
👍Premium Durability: Cables and proven to withstand over 15,000+ bends in strict laboratory tests. High-quality nylon braided wire makes the wire more durable and not easy to wind.
🤗What You Can Get: 3 Pack (10 + 10 + 10FT) Nylon Braided Design Micro USB Charging Cable. Our worry-free 18-month warranty and friendly customer service.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 23, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great micro usb charging cable!
reviews.reviewText: So far I 've been using these cables for over a week. I’m pretty sure that they are made from real braided nylon. It 's really convenient to use different lengths of cables at the bedside or at the desk. Usually I replaced the kindle paperwhite charging cable with it and it was able to charge my old stereo very quickly. (Btw, what surprised me is that these cables support data transmission and the transmission speed is satisfactory. I bought another cable once, but it does not support data transmission, and that’s why I need to buy an extra cable that supports data transmission.) They are strong cables as well, my cat has nibbled on these cords many times, but they are still working fine. I 'm surprised such a cheap price brings a reliable quality.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 4, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Solid usb to microUSB cables, 2 short, 1 medium, 1 long - great value overall
reviews.reviewText: Included in the package are two 1.5' and one 3' and a 6' USB to micro-usb cable. At least in my house, it seems like we are using microUSB devices less these days, but it also means that we have fewer of these cables laying around to use on our older devices that use these.The cables worked for data transfer and power charging, and are braided black/white as shown in the listing. The actual connectors feel well built, but don't appear to have any extra reinforcement joining the cable and the usb or micro-usb socket, where they most commonly fail.But the value on these is very good for the current price. I think it's a great deal overall, just as long as you aren't expecting super-reinforced/heavy-duty connectors.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 12, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice inexpensive cables that do the job
reviews.reviewText: This is a nice set of very inexpensive Micro USB charger cables. There are a lot of devices using this plug. Four cables: two 1.5 foot, one 3 foot, one 6 foot lengths cover almost all situations. A bargain. I tested all four cables, and they performed well. When bent, the cable stays in that position, so coiling for storage of extra wire is straight forward. It has a braided cover, which helps when handling. There is no flexibility at the head joint where the wire enters, which will likely be a point of failure if exposed to harsher treatment. I give this set of charging cables a 4.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 2, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Handy Multi-size pack
reviews.reviewText: Bottom Line:Bought this to replace a worn cable on my daughters insulin pump controller, and it fit snugly and provided proper charging. Quality seems comparable to other 'woven fabric' jacketed USB cables I've used previouslyCable came packaged in a handy baggie that was separated into pouches for the separate lengths. so far, the 'kinks' that are in the cable from being bundled are still there, but I'd expect they will smooth out over time.Its definitely handy to have a few lengths to choose from. We have a 6x port charging station in my house where I like to use short cables (so kids can't play tablets on the chargers, they have to put their screen down and do something else) so the variety was helpful.My kids are pretty tough on their micro-USB and USB-C cables, so I will follow up on this review regarding the cable's longevity, although the build quality of the cable seemed pretty solid.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Held up so far
reviews.reviewText: This came in free of charge through the Amazon Vine program. I’ve had no direct contact with Amazon Vine or the manufacturer and these opinions are my own.These cables feel well built and have held up so far! Only time will tell, but I think they'll last a while.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for device charging, inexpensive and seemingly durable
reviews.reviewText: I seem to burn through micro USB cables quickly, so I'm always picking up more.These seem much better than the cheap cables I usually grab - I'm only charging things like a Kindle or old Samsung tablet, so rarely worried about fast charging or data speeds. These work fine for that.They are stiff and a little harder to wrap up if you travel with them versus just leaving them on your deck, but hoping that means better durability as well.I'll update if I encounter any issues, but so far they seem completely functional and inexpensive.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2023
reviews.reviewText: These cables are a very good option for replacement chargers. They aren't as fast as the factory ones, but they beat the dollar store versions by a mile. Have a few length and connector options is always a plus too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 23, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good kit for the micro USB devices that are falling out of favor these days...
reviews.reviewText: Comes in three lengths that are all USB A to micro USB. I took the opportunity to grab some extra USB micro cables because I have a number of devices that still use the micro USB standard rather than the new prefered USB C connections. These are getting hard to find these days. Grab some spares so you can keep your USB micro devices charged.I knew these were wrapped in a nylon braid, but did not expect them to be quite as stiff as they are, but with use they will "wear in." I am pretty happy with these - both ends fit my devices and chargers well.
